'''smallpox'''
# {{pathology}} An [[acute]], highly [[infectious]] often [[fatal]] [[disease]] caused by a [[virus]] of the family ''[[Poxviridae]]''. It was completly [[eradicate]]d a few [[decade]]s ago. Those who survived were left with [[pockmark]]s.
